  • Deprecated Methods 
    Method and Description
    org.springframework.amqp.rabbit.connection.RabbitResourceHolder.getConnection(Class<? extends Connection>)
    Not used.
    org.springframework.amqp.rabbit.listener.MessageListenerContainer.getMessageConverter()
    - this converter is not used by the container; it was only used to configure the converter for a @RabbitListener adapter. That is now handled differently. If you are manually creating a listener container, the converter must be configured in a listener adapter (if present).
    org.springframework.amqp.rabbit.listener.AbstractMessageListenerContainer.getMessageConverter()
    org.springframework.amqp.rabbit.listener.AbstractMessageListenerContainer.getRabbitAdmin()
    in favor of AbstractMessageListenerContainer.getAmqpAdmin()
    org.springframework.amqp.rabbit.connection.RabbitResourceHolder.isFrozen()
    org.springframework.amqp.rabbit.config.NamespaceUtils.parseInnerBeanDefinition(Element, ParserContext)
    org.springframework.amqp.rabbit.listener.DirectReplyToMessageListenerContainer.setChannelAwareMessageListener(ChannelAwareMessageListener)
    org.springframework.amqp.rabbit.listener.AbstractMessageListenerContainer.setChannelAwareMessageListener(ChannelAwareMessageListener)
    use AbstractMessageListenerContainer.setMessageListener(MessageListener) since ChannelAwareMessageListener now inherits MessageListener.
    org.springframework.amqp.rabbit.core.RabbitAdmin.setDeclareCollections(boolean)
    - users should use Declarables beans instead of collections of Declarable.
    org.springframework.amqp.rabbit.config.ListenerContainerFactoryBean.setMessageConverter(MessageConverter)
    - this converter is not used by the container; it was only used to configure the converter for a @RabbitListener adapter. That is now handled differently. If you are manually creating a listener container, the converter must be configured in a listener adapter (if present).
    org.springframework.amqp.rabbit.listener.AbstractMessageListenerContainer.setMessageConverter(MessageConverter)
    - this converter is not used by the container; it was only used to configure the converter for a @RabbitListener adapter. That is now handled differently. If you are manually creating a listener container, the converter must be configured in a listener adapter (if present).
    org.springframework.amqp.rabbit.listener.DirectReplyToMessageListenerContainer.setMessageListener(Object)
    org.springframework.amqp.rabbit.listener.AbstractMessageListenerContainer.setMessageListener(Object)
    use AbstractMessageListenerContainer.setMessageListener(MessageListener).
    org.springframework.amqp.rabbit.core.RabbitTemplate.setQueue(String)
    in favor of RabbitTemplate.setDefaultReceiveQueue(String).
    org.springframework.amqp.rabbit.listener.AbstractMessageListenerContainer.setRabbitAdmin(AmqpAdmin)
    in favor of AbstractMessageListenerContainer.setAmqpAdmin(AmqpAdmin)
    org.springframework.amqp.rabbit.listener.adapter.AbstractAdaptableMessageListener.setReplyPostProcessor(MessagePostProcessor)
    in favor of AbstractAdaptableMessageListener.setBeforeSendReplyPostProcessors(MessagePostProcessor...).
